# Documentation (English only)

All docstrings, comments, AI-CORE blocks, and examples are **English**. No Russian in code-facing docs.

## Principle

Docs answer questions a reader has. If a block answers nothing, omit it.

**Two layers:** (1) **Human** module docstring — for developers only (no AI-CORE). (2) **AI-CORE** — for agents; only on **public classes** and **module-level functions** (not on the module file docstring, not on methods).

## Every file

**Line 1:** full path from `src/` as a comment, before imports and module docstring.

```python
# src/package/module.py
```

## Module docstring (human)

Fixed section order; separate sections with full-width `═` lines. Use the sections that fit the module; omit empty shells.

Typical sections:

1. **Title** — one line: `Name — purpose`.
2. **PURPOSE** — why the module exists.
3. **ARCHITECTURE / DATA FLOW** — ASCII diagram when useful.
4. Further sections (examples, philosophy, terminology) as needed.

**Do not** put `AI-CORE-BEGIN` / `AI-CORE-END` in the module docstring. Machine-readable blocks belong on classes or top-level functions.

## Classes (public)

Docstring may combine:

- Short human summary when it helps (above the block), and
- One `AI-CORE-BEGIN` … `AI-CORE-END` block with **only** structured keys (`ROLE`, `CONTRACT`, `INVARIANTS`, …). No narrative prose **inside** the AI-CORE markers.

Or AI-CORE-only when the type is self-explanatory.

## Module-level functions

May include the same `AI-CORE-BEGIN` … `AI-CORE-END` pattern as classes when the function is part of the public API.

## Methods (instance/class/static) and nested functions

Use a **single short** docstring (one line preferred), or a brief `#` comment above the `def`. No AI-CORE. Describe intent or non-obvious side effects only.

## Properties / fields

One line each when documented.

## Package `__init__.py`

Same idea as a module docstring: human sections, diagram of exports if useful; **no** AI-CORE in the package docstring itself.

## AI-CORE block (machine-readable)

Wrap with `AI-CORE-BEGIN` / `AI-CORE-END`. **Only** on public classes and module-level functions. **One to two sentences per key**; omit keys that do not apply.

**Class:**

```text
ROLE: …
CONTRACT: …
INVARIANTS: …
```

**Decorator / factory:** `PURPOSE`, `INPUT/OUTPUT`, `SIDE EFFECTS`, `FAILURES`, `ORDER`.

**Inspector:** `ROLE`, `TRAVERSAL`, `READS`, `EMITS`, `EDGES`.

## Diagram hints (module ARCHITECTURE)

Use ASCII: pipelines, phased flows, trees.

## When editing

Match surrounding file style. Do not add redundant prose. Do not put AI-CORE in module docstrings or method docstrings.
